comments: Vanderbilt (UTA) extends his arm forward and does not maintain a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Simons (POR) during the rip-through.
Eubanks (POR) places a slightly extended arm to Vanderblit's (UTA) backside and marginal contact body occurs as they disengage off ball.
Vanderbilt (UTA) and Simons (POR) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Clarkson (UTA) momentarily places his hand against Hart's (POR) front after his gather and marginal body contact occurs contesting his driving shot attempt.
Hart (POR) lightly brushes Markkanen's (UTA) arm as they both pursue the loose ball.
Clarkson (UTA) slightly extends his arm against Winslow (POR) during his drive to the basket and marginal contact occurs.

Clarkson (UTA) brings his off-arm outward and some contact occurs with Winslow's (POR) head during the driving shot attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Winslow (POR) grabs Clarkson's (UTA) shoulder during his upward shooting motion and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Vanderbilt (UTA) immediately slides his hand off of Eubanks's (POR) side and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Eubanks (POR) establishes himself in Vanderbilt's (UTA) path and absorbs the contact.
Markkanen (UTA) initiates contact with Simons's (POR) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Eubanks (POR) places his forearm to Vanderblit's (UTA) backside underneath the basket and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Eubanks (POR) brings his arm toward Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during Clarkson's (UTA) drive.
Vanderbilt (UTA) immediately slides his hand off of Simons's (POR) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Markkanen (UTA) jumps alongside Simons's (POR) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Grant (POR) and Clarkson (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Clarkson (UTA) loses control of the ball on his own, prior to Grant (POR) placing his forearm to Clarkson's (UTA) front and cleanly dislodging the ball.
Clarkson (UTA) makes contact with the ball after Hart (POR) gathers the it, and Clarkson lightly brushes his arm as two players disengage.
Vanderbilt (UTA) legally contest Hart's (POR) driving shot attempt.
Simons (POR) commits a take foul on Beasley. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Vanderbilt (UTA) moves alongside Simons's (POR) path and marginal lower body contact occurs to SImon's (POR) extended leg during the driving shot attempt.
Hart (POR) commits a take foul on Markkanen (UTA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Vanderbilt (UTA) and Simons (POR) engage and disengage with one another prior to the inbound pass.
